column13: 1. We believe the Bible to be the Inspired, the only infallible, authoritative Word of God.2. We believe that there is one God eternally existent in three persons, Father, Son and Holy Spirit.3. We believe in the Deity of our Lord Jesus Christ. In His virgin birth. In His sinless life. In His miracles. In His vicarious atoning death through His shed blood. In His bodily resurrection. In His ascension to the right hand of the Father and in His personal return in the power and glory.4. We believe that for the salvation of lost and sinful man, regeneration by the Holy Spirit is absolutely essential.5. We believe in the present ministry of the Holy Spirit by whose indwelling the Christian is enabled to live a godly life.6. We believe in the resurrection of both the saved and the lost; they that are saved unto the resurrection of life, they that are lost unto the resurrection of damnation.7. We believe in the spiritual unity of believers in our Lord Jesus Christ.

column12: Dr. Hines is a recent transplant from southern Mississippi.  He has been the pastor of First Southern Baptist since October of 2012.  He is the husband of one wife and father of two daughters.  Our pastor is a conservative, fundamental Bible believing pastor with a passion to preach God's word with fervor and compassion.  With over twenty years of ministerial experience, our pastor has a passion to spread the Gospel to the unsaved world, and lead our membership to participate in the "Great Commission" as referenced in Acts 1:8.Our pastor has several earned degrees from Jacksonville Baptist Theological Seminary, Jacksonville, FL. and New Orleans Baptist Theological Seminary, New Orleans, LA.Pastor Tim is an outdoorsman!  He has fallen in love with California's beautiful landscape and has already caught his share of trout from several "secret" fishing holes!May God use our combined talents to reach our community with the Gospel of Christ and share his love wherever we go.

column12: Dave grew up in the north of England where he first remembers hearing the Gospel at a local football stadium as Billy Graham was preaching. It was there in 1984 that Dave received Christ as his Lord and Saviour.Before heading to college, Dave attended Capernwray Hall Bible School where he learnt many of the most important lessons for living daily in Gods will. While later serving as the Director of Outreach in the Bible School, Dave met his wife, Sadie. They enjoyed several years ministering together before moving with their two children to California in 2008.God's Word is central to Dave and his families’ daily life, and is the reason he regards it a privilege to serve at Calvary San Ramon in Bible teaching as well as the training and equipping of the fellowship to spread the Good news of Jesus to those God has put in our lives. Romans 1:16 reminds Dave that as His people we have a responsibility to put Jesus first while serving Him with our entire lives; “For I am not ashamed of the gospel, because it is the power of God that brings salvation to everyone who believes: first to the Jew, then to the Gentile.“Dave has a special interest in science and has enjoyed teaching many seminars based on the topics of Creation and Evolution. It is Dave’s passionate belief that the world of science points directly to a wonderful, creator God.

column13: Grace Church is a Presbyterian, Bible-believing church with an optimistic understanding of Christ's final victory over the world. We believe God works through covenants and will bless us or curse us as a church and as a nation according to our obedience or lack thereof. We know that Christ commands us not only to stand against the wiles of the devil (Eph. 611), but also to make disciples of all nations (Matt. 289), being the salt of the earth and the light of the world. It is our goal to know God's Word so that we can please our Lord and Savior in all areas of our lives.

column38: 8:30 am Informal serviceThe 8:30 service at Hillsdale United Methodist Church welcomes all who wish to participate in a more informal worship experience. Held in the Peterson Room, the hour long program includes lay leadership, caring and sharing, prayer, scripture, music, a sermon and an opportunity to discuss the sermon. The interactive nature of the worship service helps build close friendships and allows for a rich variety of worship experiences. Come and join us in this more informal setting as we worship and explore our faith together.11:00 am Traditional serviceThis is traditional worship service held in the Sanctuary. The service includes lively congregational singing, scripture readings, prayers and sermon. At times, we have have Hand Bell Choir and scripture dramatization by Sunday School Children. The first Sunday of the month is Communion Sunday, and the Tongan choir sings at this service.2:00 pm Tongan language serviceSo, if you are Tongan -- this service is in YOUR language. The format is the traditional, formal Tongan service replete with the terrific Tongan Choir and Preachers from the Tongan community. IF you are not Tongan -- we do offer a translation capability through our audio/headphones. So if you would like to experience a very formal, but sincerely spiritual service, followed by a terrific feast.... you are warmly invited!

column13: We believe:The Bible is the inspired Word of God, authoritative, and the only infallible rule of faith and practice. There is one God, infinite in glory, wisdom, holiness, justice, power and love, eternally existent as Father, Son, and Holy Spirit. In the deity of Jesus Christ, Second person of the Godhead. He was conceived of the Holy Spirit, born of the Virgin Mary; lived a sinless life; performed miracles; through His atoning death, paid for the sins of the world; in His bodily resurrection; ascension to the right hand of the Father; and His future personal return in power and glory.In the Holy Spirit, third person of the Godhead. column14: We are  L.I.V.E.:   Loving,  Intellectual,  Visionary and  Empowering. Our congregation is made of people who are at many different stages in their faith: exploring, growing, struggling, unshakable and everywhere in between. We believe that it’s not about “having it together”, but rather “living it together”. As a community, we are figuring out what it means to walk with Jesus in this world today. Whether you are a parent, college student, child, young adult or more mature, we seek to apply Jesus’ teachings as faithfully as we can so we may impact the communities in which we live.

column15: Urban Grace is a church that seeks to live in view of the Gospel as a city within the city – understanding culture, loving people, and displaying the Glory of God with our transformed lives.  We would love for you to join us in this glorious God-given task of making disciples who make disciples.
column38: The service begins with a few announcements, followed by a time of quiet reflection and prayer. A music team leads us in a few songs, we read a passage of Scripture, and then we pray for the world, nation, state, city, other churches, and Urban Grace.  The sermon is based on the Bible and is designed to help us understand God, who we are, and the world we live in. After the sermon, we spend time in SMALL_GROUPS discussing and applying the sermon, and praying for one another. The service ends with a benediction to send people off with a ‘good word’ of encouragement.  In addition, on the first Sunday of every month, we also celebrate communion, to thank God and remind ourselves of our love and need for Jesus Christ.  Typically, our service goes from 10 AM to noon.Essentially, we aim to sing to Christ, pray to Christ, preach Christ, and be on mission with Christ!After service people often spend 30-45 minutes greeting with one another and then frequently go in groups to lunch.

column12: Randy Walters and his wife, Nancy,  were both born and raised in the Bay Area. In  fact they currently live in the same house his parents owned for many years.     Randy graduated from Simpson College when it was at San Francisco, majoring in Biblical Studies. Immediately after finishing his college degree he married Nancy and moved to La Mirada to attend Talbot School of Theology. He finally graduated with a Master of Divinity (M.Div.) after taking virtually all the Old Testament electives offered over  6 years! Yes, He really studied Hebrew, Aramaic and Akkadian.  Recently Randy completed the Master of Theology (Th.M.) degree at Golden Gate Baptist Seminary, again with an emphasis in Old Testament.   Randy and Nancy have five adult children. He has many hobbies including cycling and oil painting. Nancy is a gifted seamstress and especially enjoys making quilts.
column13: Statement of FaithWe believe in one God who alone is to be worshipped, who rules the universe and created everything. He has revealed Himself as Father, Son and Holy Spirit.We believe in the Father: Holy, Almighty and loving, the source of all goodness, truth and life.We believe in the Son, one with the Father, our Lord Jesus Christ who was sent into the world by the Father's love, conceived by the Spirit and born of the virgin Mary. He was crucified for our sins and raised from the dead by the power of God. He now sits at the Father's right hand praying and advocating for His Church and will return to judge everyone on earth. Then every knee will bow before Him in honor and every person will agree that Jesus always has been, is now, and always will be Lord.We believe in the Holy Spirit, one with the Father and Son, who inspired the Scriptures, who by His grace brings to new spiritual birth all who believe in Jesus through repentance, who lives in them as a guarantee of eternal life, empowers them for holy living and loving relationships, and distributes to them gifts of power for service and ministry.We believe that human beings were created in God's image, but were alienated from God because of sin and now live in a sin-damaged world. We, therefore, are unable to restore the broken relationship ourselves. God, in His love and mercy, through Jesus' sacrifice on the cross, restores those who believe and repent, giving them a new birth, new identity, and new nature.We believe God brings all His new-born children into His family, the Church. This eternal body is revealed in the local church wherever His people gather for worship, relationship, teaching, and service around His Word. As Lord of His Church, Jesus directs us to tell everyone everywhere about Him so that they too might follow Him and be saved from eternal judgment. One day He will come and gather all His Church to be with Him in heaven's glory forever.We believe that the Church is the body of Jesus on earth and God's family. Through these family relationships, God utilizes His Spirit to promote unity, to cause healing, to exercise His gifts, and to mobilize a great army of Christ-followers who join with Him in the fight against the evil, demonic powers of darkness at work both in our world here and in the heavenly places.We believe in the Bible as God's inspired, timeless and relevant Word to all people. In it He reveals the truth which we believe and commit to follow. It is completely trustworthy and our authoritative guide for conduct as individuals, as families and as a Church.

column13: Doctrinal StatementIn order to identify Calvary Chapel Hayward as conservative in theology, and evangelical is spirit, we set forth this statement of fundamental beliefs:1. We believe the Bible to be the inspired, the only infallible, authoritative Word of God and inerrant in the original writings.2. We believe that there is one God, eternally existent in three persons, Father, Son, & Holy Spirit3. We believe in the deity of our Lord Jesus Christ, in His virgin birth, in His sinless life, in His miracles, that He died in our place and through His shed blood we receive the forgiveness of sins, in His bodily resurrection, in His ascension to the right hand of the Father, and in His personal return in power and glory.4. We believe that lost and sinful man must be saved from this condition, and that man’s only hope of redemption is through the shed blood of Jesus Christ, the Son of God.5. We believe in the present ministry of the Holy Spirit by whose indwelling the Christian is enabled to live the Christian life.6. We believe in the resurrection of both the saved and the unsaved; they that are saved unto a resurrection of life and they that are unsaved unto a resurrection of damnation.7. We believe in the spiritual unity of believers in our Lord Jesus Christ.Statement of Distinctives we hold to:• The inerrancy of Scripture• The present day continuation of the spiritual gifts that Paul wrote of in 1 Corinthians 12-14• Simplicity in church government, rather than a complex bureaucracy• A dependence upon the Holy Spirit to lead, rather than ambitious promotion of someone’s agenda• The premillennial, pre-tribulation return of Christ for His waiting church• The verse by verse teaching of the Word of God in such a way that it leads toward spiritual maturityYou Will NOT Find at Calvary Chapel• The teaching of ‘positive confession’• The belief that true Christians can be possessed by demons• A fatalistic Calvinistic view which allows no room for free will• Prophecy that supersedes Scripture• The incorporation of humanistic psychology and philosophy into Biblical teaching• "Charismania" (the over emphasis upon spiritual gifts, experiential signs and wonders, etc.)
column15: Calvary Chapel Hayward is a non-denominational Christian fellowship in the heart of the Bay Area which exists to love God, to be taught by His Word, and to reach out to people with the love of Jesus Christ in the power of the Holy Spirit. It is our desire to:Grow in our relationship with God through the knowledge of His grace and truth.Grow in our relationships with one another.Let the world know of God's love for them as demonstrated in the cross of Jesus Christ."FOR WE DO NOT PREACH OURSELVES, BUT CHRIST JESUS THE LORD."2 CORINTHIANS 4:5On Sunday morning we have contemporary worship, verse by verse Bible teaching, & children’s ministry. column15: One of the most often asked questions we hear here at Apostolic Christian Center is. “What kind of Church is this?” Maybe the question stems from the liveliness of our worship celebrations and the excitement felt while in our services. But to answer their question, we are a welcoming fellowship of believers who are deeply committed to the Biblical Truths which Jesus Christ taught His Disciples and then those same Disciples taught the First Century Church after the Day of Pentecost.Within our congregation you will find children, youth, adults and seniors. In our Fellowship you will find young families with children and even some generations of families that have been part of the local church since the 1940’s and 1950’s. You will also find many who have never had a prior church experience of any kind. We are determined to say.”Welcome! You’re going to like it here” to all whom Jesus also welcomes and receives! Our worship to God is from the heart, filled with passion and joy and always in spirit and in truth. Come and join us in any of our celebrations and I am sure you will feel the Presence of God as you help us “lift Him Higher in Praise”. This year our focus is upon teaching, preaching and worshipping Him with a Fresh Anointing. God has a purpose for your life. Come and discover the Joy He gives.In His Love,Pastor Abel E. Rodriguez, Th.B

column14: Faith Community Church is a community of Christian disciples — real people who love God, love others, and follow Jesus in service by seeking to grow the Kingdom of God. Everything we do at Faith Community Church serves one purpose:  To build the family of God by bringing people to God, building people of God, and serving people for God.Bringing People to God:  Through corporate worship services, events, and personal/individual interaction we encourage non-believers and believers alike to encounter God more deeply whether by accepting Christ as their Savior and Lord, or by growing in their love, trust, and knowledge of God.Building People of God:  Through small group experiences, Sunday school classes and Bible exploration, regular fellowship events, prayer groups, discipling relationships, and other ministries we encourage continued personal growth in the love of God while fostering love for one another as members of His family.Serving People for God:  Service to God is service to others. We will afford members the opportunity to fulfill their Kingdom purpose through meaningful ministry in order to bring people to God and support them as they proceed through the journey of faith.

column12: Tim Royal received his bachelor's degree from Simpson University and his Master of Divinity from Golden Gate Baptist Theological Seminary where he is currently working on his Doctor of Ministry. He has pastored for the last seventeen years. He is the recipient of the LifeWay Pastoral Leadership Award; Wright-Bramlett Christian Leadership Award and Who’s Who in American Colleges and Universities.Pastor Tim has been Senior Pastor at Halcyon Baptist Church since January 2007. Pastor Tim is passionate about the sense of community at Halcyon which is reflected in our simple purpose statement which is:"Halcyon Baptist Church exists to raise up disciples who:Love GodLove One AnotherLove All People"Family is huge for Pastor Tim as is demonstrated by his deep love for his wife of 30 years, Janet Lee and their four children. This is also demonstrated by his commitment to his church family. His door and his heart are open to all who need him, and he strives to see that his values for spiritual family and community are the heart and soul of Halcyon Baptist Church.His life verse is (ask him about it sometime):Jeremiah 29:11 (NIV)"I know the plans I have for you,' declares the Lord, 'Plans to prosper you and not to harm you. Plans to give you a hope and a future."
column13: At Halcyon Baptist Church we believe:1. That the local church was established by God to form a Community that aggressively lives out and seeks to expand the Kingdom of God on earth through the rule of Love as demonstrated by Jesus Himself.2. That Jesus Christ literally died for our sins and rose bodily from the dead as atonement on our behalf before His Holy Father and that a personal relationship with Him is the only way to God (John 14:6).3. That there is only One God. He exists in three persons: The Father, Son, and Holy Spirit. The Holy Spirit's empowerment and filling should be continually sought through walking in right relationship with God.4. That God Himself entered history as a man, while remaining completely God. That man was Jesus Christ, born a Jew of the line of David, born of a virgin, and fulfilling all of the hundreds of prophecies concerning Him found in the scripture.5. That Scripture is without error in its original manuscripts. That Scripture is God’s holy word making it authoritative and powerful in men and women’s lives.6. That Marriage is between one man and one woman and that we will refuse to perform or even to recognize any other form of marriage as defined by a fallen world. Our denomination has prepared a statement of generally held convictions called The Baptist Faith and Message. It serves as a guide to understanding who we are.
column14: Halcyon Baptist Church exists to make disciples of Christ who:Love GodLove One AnotherLove All PeopleWe believe that a deeper understanding of life, its purpose and its meaning come through these three intertwined paths and that love is not primarily a feeling, but rather is primarily demonstrated by unselfish deeds and behavior.

column13: We are part of the greater work of God known as the Christian and Missionary Alliance (C&MA). Our Statement of Faith:There is one God, who is infinitely perfect, existing eternally in three persons: Father, Son, and Holy Spirit.Jesus Christ is the true God and the true man. He was conceived by the Holy Spirit and born of the virgin Mary. He died upon the cross, the Just for the unjust, as a substitutionary sacrifice, and all who believe in Him are justified on the ground of His shed blood. He arose from the dead according to the Scriptures. His now at the right hand of Majesty on high as our great High Priest. He will com again to establish His kingdom, righteousness and peace.The Holy Spirit is a divine person, sent to indwell, guide teach, empower the believer, and convince the world of sin, of righteousness, and of judgment.The Old and New Testaments, inerrant as originally given, were verbally inspired by God and are a complete revelation of His will for the salvation of men. They constitute the divine and only rule of Christian faith and practice.Man was originally created in the image and likeness of God: he fell through disobedience, incurring thereby both physical and spiritual death. All men are born with a sinful nature, are separated from the life of God, and can be saved only through the atoning work of the Lord Jesus Christ. The portion of the unrepentant and unbelieving is existence forever in conscious torment; and that of the believer, in everlasting joy and bliss.Salvation has been provided through Jesus Christ for all men; and those who repent and believe in Him are born again of the Holy Spirit, receive the gift of eternal, and become the children of God.It is the will of God that each believer should be filled with the Holy Spirit and be sanctified wholly, being separated from sin and the world and fully dedicated to the will of God, thereby receiving power for holy living and effective service. This is both a crisis and a progressive experience wrought in the life of the believer subsequent to conversion.Provision is made in the redemptive work of the Lord Jesus Christ for the healing of the mortal body. Prayer for the sick and anointing with oil are taught in the Scriptures and are privileges for the Church in this present age.The Church consists of all those who believe on the Lord Jesus Christ, are redeemed through His blood, and are born again of the Holy Spirit. Christ is the head of the Body, the Church, which has been commissioned by Him to go into all the world as a witness, preaching the gospel to all nations. The local church is a body of believers in Christ who are joined together for the worship of God, for edification through the Word of God, for prayer, fellowship, the proclamation of the gospel, and observance of the ordinances of Baptism and the Lord's Supper.There shall be a bodily resurrection of the just and of the unjust; for the former, a resurrection unto life; for the latter, a resurrection unto judgment.The second coming of the Lord Jesus Christ is imminent and will be personal, visible and premillennial. This is the believer's blessed hope and is a vital truth which is an incentive to holy living and faithful service.
column14: The purpose of Hillside Alliance and the C&MA is to build a Great Commission of churches that reach out to their community with the Good News of Jesus Christ and pool their resources to send missionaries throughout the world with the same message. Our Vision is to be used by God to make a difference in our families, our workplaces, our community, and the world. We encourage spiritual growth by teaching, coaching and through Celebrate Recovery Biblical 12 steps for hurts, habits and hang-ups. We model service to the "lest of these" being Jesus in Disguise for others and seeing Jesus in the lives of those we serve. We covenant together:To be authenticTo serve a cause greater than themselvesTo create communityTo be generous and practice hospitalityTo work righteously as a way of being sent by God into the world

column12: As a San Francisco Bay Area resident all his life, Pastor David Clift knows both the stresses and opportunities that afford us in the East Bay. Born and raised in Concord, David grew up in what was a very functional home. He fought with his brother and two sisters, argued with his parents, and often struggled in school. Life was good. Life was "normal." Then in 1972, when David was 10, life changed. David's family had never gone to church much, but someone invited them one Sunday and they heard a message that would change their lives forever.  David that heard that Jesus died and rose for him and that he could be forgiven for all of his wrong and become part of God’s family simply by accepting what Jesus had done. David became a follower of Christ and life took an exciting turn. David prayed about what God would have him do with his life.  Since he was very young, David had always dreamed of being a lawyer, but by his junior year of high school, he knew God wanted him to pastor. David went on to college to earn a BA in Bible and a BA in Speech. Grad school led him to an MA in Biblical Studies and an MDiv. While in graduate school, David met his wife at a church in Martinez, where he was an Associate Pastor.  About four months after Cindy and David became engaged, Hillside Baptist Church (Hillside Church) contacted David and asked if he would consider coming as their pastor.  The church had declined and was deeply concerned for their welfare.  David came in September of 1989 and Cindy and David were married in October of 1989.  David continues as lead pastor.  David and Cindy now have three amazing daughters.  David enjoys running, kick boxing, water sports, snow skiing, and travelling.  Most of all, he loves sharing the greatest message of all with people.
column13: The Essentials We Believe1. ABOUT GOD. God is the Creator and Ruler of the universe. He has eternally existed in three personalities: The Father, The Son, and The Holy Spirit. These three are co-equal and are one God. Genesis 1;1, 26,27; 3:22; Psalm 90:2; Matthew 28:19; I Peter 1:2; II Corinthians 13:14 2. ABOUT JESUS. Jesus Christ is the Son of God. He is co-equal with the Father. Jesus lived a sinless human life and offered Himself as the perfect sacrifice for the sins of all people by dying on a cross. He arose from the dead after three days to demonstrate His power over sin and death. He ascended to Heaven’s glory and will return again someday to earth to reign as King of Kings, and Lord of Lords. Matthew 1:22,23; Isaiah 9:6; John 1:1-5, 14:10-30; Hebrews 4:14,15; I Corinthians 15:3, 4; Romans 1:3, 4; Acts 1:9-11; I Timothy 6:14,15; Titus 2:13 3. ABOUT THE HOLY SPIRIT. The Holy Spirit is co-equal with the Father and the Son of God. He is present in the world to make men aware of their need for Jesus Christ. He also lives in every Christian from the moment of salvation. He provides the Christian with power for living, understanding of spiritual truth, and guidance in doing what is right. He gives every believer a spiritual gift when they are saved. As Christians we seek to live under His control daily. II Corinthians 3:17; John 16:7-13, 14:16,17; Acts 1:8; I Corinthians 2:12, 3:16; Ephesians 1:13; Galatians 5:25; Ephesians 5:184. ABOUT THE BIBLE.The Bible is God’s Word to us. It was written by human authors, under the supernatural guidance of the Holy Spirit. It is the supreme source of truth for Christian beliefs and living. Because it is inspired by God, it is the truth without any mixture of error. II Timothy 3:16; II Peter 1:20,21; II Timothy 1:13; Psalm 119:105, 160; 12:6; Proverbs 30:55. ABOUT HUMAN BEINGS. People are made in the spiritual image of God, to be like Him in character. People are the supreme object of God’s creation. Although every person has tremendous potential for good, all of us are marred by an attitude of disobedience toward God called “sin.” This attitude separates people from God and causes many problems in life.Genesis 1:27; Psalm 8:3-6; Isaiah 53:6a; Romans 3:23;Isaiah 59:1, 26. ABOUT SALVATION.Salvation is God’s free gift to us but we must accept it. We can never make up for our sin by self-improvement or good works. Only by trusting in Jesus Christ as God’s offer of forgiveness can anyone be saved from sin’s penalty. When we turn from our self-ruled life and turn to Jesus in faith we are saved. Eternal life begins the moment one receives Jesus Christ into his life by faith.Romans 6:23; Ephesians 2:8-9; John 14:6, 1:12; Titus 3:5; Galatians 3:26; Romans 5:17. ABOUT ETERNAL SECURITY.Because God gives us eternal life through Jesus Christ, the true believer is secure in that salvation for eternity. If you have been genuinely saved, you cannot “lose” it. Salvation is maintained by the grace and power of God, not by the self-effort of the Christian. It is the grace and keeping power of God that gives us this security.John 10:29; II Timothy 1:12; Hebrews 7:25, 10:10,14; I Peter 1:3-58. ABOUT ETERNITY.People were created to exist forever. We will either exist eternally separated from God by sin, or eternally with God through forgiveness and salvation. To be eternally separated from God is Hell. To be eternally in union with Him is eternal life. Heaven and Hell are real places of eternal existence.John 3:16, 2:25, 5:11-13; Romans 6:23; Revelation 20:15; Matthew 1:8, 2:44, 46
column14: H.I.L.L.S.I.D.E. Strategy8 Principles That Make Our Church UniqueHEADSHIP OF CHRIST.Everything we do is designed to communicate Jesus Christ as our Savior and Lord. Christ will always be the focal point of our ministry and mission.Ephesians 1:22, 23 “And He put all things under His feet, and gave Him to be head over all things to the church, 23 which is His body, the fullness of Him who fills all in all.” (NKJV)INSPIRING SERVICES.Psalm 149:1 “Praise the LORD! Sing to the LORD a new song, And His praise in the assembly of saints.” (NKJV)LOVING ACCEPTANCE.Romans 15:7 “Wherefore, accept one another, just as Christ also accepted us to the glory of God.” (NASV)LAY MINISTRY.Romans 12:4, 5 “For as we have many members in one body, but all the members do not have the same function, 5 so we, being many, are one body in Christ, and individually members of one another.” (NKJV)SIMPLE STRUCTURE.I Corinthians 14:40 “Let all things be done decently and in order.” (NKJV)INVITATIONAL ADVERTISING.Matthew 5:14-16 “Ye are the light of the world. A city that is set on an hill cannot be hid. 15 Neither do men light a candle, and put it under a bushel, but on a candlestick; and it giveth light unto all that are in the house. 16 Let your light so shine before men, that they may see your good works, and glorify your Father which is in heaven.” (KJV)DEFINED PURPOSE.To Celebrate God’s Presence; Demonstrate God’s Love; Communicate God’s Word; and Educate God’s People.Acts 13:36 “For David, after he had served the purpose of God in his own generation, fell asleep...” (NASV)ENCOURAGING PREACHING.Romans 15:4 “For whatever things were written before were written for our learning, that we through the patience and comfort of the Scriptures might have hope.” (NKJV)

column12: Pastor Matthew L. Ellis served for 3 years as Associate Pastor at Balboa Baptist Church (San Francisco, CA) while he was completing his Masters in Divinity from Golden Gate Baptist Theological Seminary.  In late 2008 he stepped down from that position when he moved and took on a full-time job as a Bible Teacher at Fremont Christian School (a ministry of Harbor Light Church, Fremont, CA).  In 2009 started attending Hillview Baptist Church as an active lay-leader in February, moving to the Associate Pastor role in August, serving under their excellent Senior Pastor, Ron Standifer.  He continued to serve in this position until late 2011 when he stepped up to Interim Pastor as Pastor Standifer's health began to fail and he then joined our Heavenly Father.  Pastor Ellis also serves as an Air Force Reserve chaplain. Once a month, the strong lay-leadership is seen in this church as they rise up to continue worshiping God as their head pastor is gone and a guest preacher comes in.

column14: Our Mission: To be a church that brings glory to God.  To reach the culturally diverse population of Union City, the Tri-City Area, and the world with the Good News of Jesus Christ.  To help all our members to reach their full potential in God by helping them to develop a lifestyle of worship, evangelism, discipleship, fellowship, and ministry.Core Values:  - We believe that God has a purpose for our church and that He will guide us to accomplish it. - We believe that our ministry focus should be on people, and that the greatest need of people is a personal, growing relationship with Jesus Christ. - We believe the Bible is the foundation of our faith, doctrine, and practice and that it is relevant to our lives in the 21st century. - We further hold to the essentials of the Christian faith to be core values such as, the Triune Godhead; salvation by grace through faith; that scripture is inspired, inerrant word of God; and other essentials of the Christian faith.Our Vision: Helping people reach their full potential in God.We...  - Relate to another though fellowship - Edify each other through discipleship - Adoration of our Lord in worship - Communicate the Gospel through evangelism - Help our church and community through ministry
column15: Welcome to our page & thank you for 'stopping by!'  For over 50 years Hillview Baptist Church has been a community of faith serving the Union City, Hayward, and Fremont area.  I'd like to personally invite you to come and join us as we seek to reach people for Jesus Christ & grow them in His likeness.  You can connect with us through our worship celebration, our small group meetings, or more!  Our hope is that you will feel right at home with us.  If you are searching for a church home, we'd like you to know that there's a place just for you here at Hillview Baptist Church.We hope to see you soon! With Faith in Jesus Christ, Matthew Ellis, Interim Pastor

column15: Greetings in Christ Jesus,Welcome to our humble website. This media is provided as a means of communication, both internally with the church, as well as discourse we introduce ourselves to you. We hope this website can be a blessing to you.Community Christian Church of Indonesia was established in 1999 with a vision to reach and serve the people of Indonesia in the San Francisco Bay Area, as well as student / i Indonesia at Diablo Valley College is devoted close to our first branch in Concord. We are Indonesian-speaking congregation under the auspices of the Church of the Nazarene, who believe in the triune God, the divinity of Jesus Christ, who died to redeem the sins of mankind and then rose again to conquer death, and the absolute authority of the Bible as the revealed Word of God to man.Salam sejahtera di dalam Kristus Yesus,Selamat datang di website sederhana kami. Media ini disediakan sebagai sarana komunikasi, baik secara internal dengan jemaat, juga sebagai wacana memperkenalkan diri kami kepada Saudara. Kami harap website ini dapat menjadi berkat bagi Saudara.Gereja Kristen Komunitas Indonesia didirikan pada tahun 1999 dengan visi menjangkau dan melayani masyarakat Indonesia di San Francisco Bay Area, juga mahasiswa/i Indonesia di Diablo Valley College yand dekat dengan cabang pertama kami di Concord. Kami merupakan jemaat berbahasa Indonesia di bawah naungan Church of the Nazarene, yang percaya akan Allah Tritunggal, keilahian Yesus Kristus yang telah mati menebus dosa manusia dan kemudian bangkit kembali mengalahkan maut, dan otoritas mutlak Alkitab sebagai Firman yang diturunkan Allah kepada manusia.

column12: My wife, Leighton, and I grew up, went to school, were married, and had our first child in Lexington, Kentucky. We moved to San Jose, California in February, 1977 with our first child just barely over one year old. Since then we have had three additional children and now have seven grandchildren. I joined the pastoral staff of Kingsway in 1981 and became the senior pastor in 1990. Leighton has been an Art teacher at Valley Christian High School for over twenty years and enjoys the rare opportunities she gets from time to time to do her own artwork. When our schedules permit, we have fun taking rides on our Harley Davidson. We have logged thousands of miles together with our most memorable trips being the old Route 66 from Chicago to Santa Monica and a trip to Sturgis, South Dakota for Bike Week after visting of the Grand Tetons and Yellowstone National Park. Our passion is to create an atmosphere of family as we build Christian community with our friends at Kingsway. We believe God is just as active in the world today as He was when the church was first born over two thousand years ago. His Holy Spirit is still working to transform lives, marriages, families, neighborhoods, and whole communities.
column13: We believe in... • The one true God who lives eternally in three persons – the Father, the Son and the Holy Spirit. • The love, grace and sovereignty of God in creating, sustaining, ruling, redeeming and judging the world.• The divine inspiration and supreme authority of the Old and New Testament Scriptures, which are the written Word of God – fully trustworthy for faith and conduct.• The dignity of all people, made male and female in God’s image to love, be holy and care for creation, yet corrupted by sin, which incurs divine wrath and judgement. • The incarnation of God’s eternal Son, the Lord Jesus Christ – born of the virgin Mary; truly divine and truly human, yet without sin. • The atoning sacrifice of Christ on the cross: dying in our place, paying the price of sin and defeating evil, so reconciling us with God. • The bodily resurrection of Christ, the first fruits of our resurrection; his ascension to the Father, and his reign and mediation as the only Savior of the world. • The justification of sinners solely by the grace of God through faith in Christ. • The ministry of God the Holy Spirit, who leads us to repentance, unites us with Christ through new birth, empowers our discipleship and enables our witness. • The Church, the body of Christ both local and universal, the priesthood of all believers – given life by the Spirit and endowed with the Spirit’s gifts to worship God and proclaim the gospel, promoting justice and love. • The personal and visible return of Jesus Christ to fulfil the purposes of God, who will raise all people to judgement, bring eternal life to the redeemed and eternal condemnation to the lost, and establish a new heaven and new earth
column14: We are committed to... • Living in the SpiritWe believe that the life of God comes to us through the Holy Spirit. We want to experience God’s manifest presence as we worship and pray in the Holy Spirit. We see the Holy Spirit’s ministry and gifts in the life of the believer and the church as a key to holiness, fruitfulness and effective mission, as every member is thoroughly filled with the Spirit, walks in step with the Spirit, and flows in the anointing and ministry of the Spirit.• Building the churchWe believe that God plans to change the world through His church, the Body of Christ. We therefore want to see relationship at the heart of how we are called to build together: celebration of believers’ baptisms and breaking of bread at the center of our fellowship, the release of every-member ministry and Ephesians 4 ministries as keys to God’s mission, and church-planting as a call of God in expanding His kingdom.• Seeking the KingdomChrist’s primary call on our lives is to be a people who are centered on Him and seeking His Kingdom. We therefore are determined to seek God’s Kingdom 24/7, in our families, at work, in leisure, and in the family of the church. We want to keep being transformed to be like the King. We want to preach, live and demonstrate the gospel of the Kingdom, attending to issues of injustice, poverty and bondage in society.• Focusing on missionWe believe that God is on a mission to demonstrate his love to His world, to redeem the world from its sin, and to gather a huge family to himself from across the nations. As God’s people, we must be on the same mission. Therefore we want to be proclaiming the Good News; demonstrating the Good News in every aspect of culture and society; seeing lives transformed by the power of Jesus; living the Good News.We are characterized by...  • RelationshipEverything in the Body of Christ is relational! We believe brother/sister relationships, pastor/disciple relationships and small group relationships are key to the life of the church family. • FamilyGod works through spiritual and natural family to give us a place of belonging, love, joy, security, friendship, vision, and care. Fatherhood and motherhood are key to strong, healthy families! There is a joint mandate for men and women to rule together within families. We also recognize the spiritual headship of men within family. Our churches appoint men to be elders, but are also clear that women have an important place of leadership in our church families, just as in our natural families. • Leadership Anointed servant leadership, as Jesus taught it and modelled it, is vital to build up everyone in the body of Christ, and help all to grow to full maturity and fulfil their God-given destiny. We recognize the importance of spiritual fatherhood. This is a vital aspect of apostolic ministry and is a key to building family. The model for all leadership is Jesus himself!• GenerosityGenerous living and giving is a key to individuals and communities enjoying the blessing of God. Tithing is a starting point for giving, but generosity will take us far beyond that. We encourage the practice of tithing to the local church of which we are part, where we are cared for spiritually. We see tithes as sustaining the ministry of church and mission, and offerings for good works, buildings etc.• DiscipleshipDiscipleship is a key to growing all of God’s people into maturity, so that each one can play their full part in the purposes of God’s Kingdom. We encourage strongly the fostering of relationships of discipleship, where personal pastoring and mentoring are key. In our view, this is essential.• Ephesians 4 ministryWe believe that receiving apostles, prophets, evangelists, pastors and teachers into local churches brings increased vision and spiritual impact, and provides good care, counsel and accountability for local church leaders.• Wider relationshipsWe encourage an atmosphere of working together with other churches. We believe that it is one mark of healthy churches to relate to and receive from others. This enables the wider Body of Christ to be built up, and allows Christ’s mission to be more fruitful.• DiversityWe value the diversity of leadership and different models of church. We believe this helps us to understand and enjoy the richness of the body of Christ, and we want to live in an atmosphere of respect and mutual appreciation. This diversity is a positive, edifying feature of the Body of Christ!
column15: Kingsway is a warm and friendly congregation that purposes to experience authentic Christian community in this busy world we live in today. We would love to welcome you to into our spiritual family and we look forward to getting to know you.

column12: I was born and raised in Rossland, British Columbia, where I loved music, skiing, and mountain climbing.  My husband Dan and I met at MIT, where we both got doctorates in chemistry.  We have three children, and found Lakeside Temple when we went church shopping many years ago.  The peace was compelling, and the teachings were enlightening.I worked for Chevron for 16 years, leaving when our youngest child was a year old.  I took all the Temple classes just because I wanted to learn to live more effectively.  Eventually I was ordained (in 2000) and became Minister in 2001.  I love my job, and I enjoy our weekly singing workshop, led by our choral director and voice coach, Dieter Erbelding.
column13: God is love. Through prayer and meditation, we come to realize how to live more freely, fully, and peacefully. We understand we are intended to be happy and prosperous on this spiritual journey of living on the earth. We may make mistakes, yet as we know better, we do better. Jesus proved for us that Life is good and Life never ends.We believe our own thoughts help to shape and form our outer circumstances. As we think, so we experience.  As Jesus said, "As a man thinketh in his heart, so is he."
column14: Lakeside Temple is a place of deep Peace, where we feel Spirit flowing freely. Here, we- become quiet and let Spirit speak.- think about what we really want, and let ourselves receive it.- find true ability to accomplish.- learn to stay with Divine Love and cooperate with Divine Law.As we realize our unlimited spiritual nature, we learn to live abundantly and fully, accepting the bounty of our loving God.
column15: Lakeside Temple is full of peace.  Here is a refuge.  And here is a place to learn to meditate, so you can feel your peace no matter what appears to be happening.

column13: What We Believe It has been said, “To keep the faith, we must know the faith.” We encourage all those attending any church to study the Word of God. Dig deep. Ask questions. Know what you believe. We have briefly outlined below several key beliefs that are essential to an active Christian life. top1. We believe the Bible is God’s Word given by divine inspiration, the record of God’s revelation of Himself to humanity (II Timothy 3:16). top2. We believe in the one living and true God, perfect in wisdom, sovereignty, holiness, justice, mercy and love (I Timothy 1:17; Psalm 86:15; Deuteronomy 32:3-4). top3. We believe God created an order of spiritual beings called angels to serve Him and do His will (Psalm 148:1-5; Colossians 1:16). top4. We believe God created man in His own image to have fellowship with Himself and to be steward over His creation (Genesis 1:26-28). top5. We believe salvation is redemption by Christ of the whole person from sin and death (II Timothy 1:9-10; I Thessalonians 5:23). top6. We believe the Church is the body of which Christ is the head and all who believe in Him are members (Ephesians 1:22-23; Romans 12:4-5). top7. We believe religious liberty, rooted in Scripture, is the inalienable right of all individuals to freedom of conscience with ultimate accountability to God (Genesis 1:27; John 8:32; II Corinthians 3:17; Romans 8:21; Acts 5:29). top8. We believe Christians, individually and collectively, are salt and light in society (Matthew 5:13-16). top9. We believe God, in His own time and in His own way, will bring all things to their appropriate end and establish the new heaven and the new earth (Ephesians 1:9-10, Revelation 21:1). top

column12: Josh and Cecil Wroten grew up in the Silicon Valley. They met in high school and later married in June of 2000. After graduating in May of 2002 from Trinity Baptist College in Florida, they returned to the Bay Area to start Morning Star Church in Newark. They have a vision to develop a multi-ethnic church community where people can find real answers to life’s problems. They have been blessed with two children, Alanna Joy and Ethan Luke. Josh has a Master of Divinity degree from Golden Gate Seminary.Josh also serves as the Director of Church Planting for Next Generation Churches of Northern California and Nevada (www.nextgenchurches.com). He loves encouraging church planters to maintain a healthy balance between ministry, family, and spiritual life. Locally, he serves on the board for CityServe, the tri-cities association of pastors and churches that are committed to meeting the needs of the community in the name of Jesus.
column13: The TrinityWe believe in one eternal God, the source and goal of life, who exists as three persons in the Trinity: the Father, the Son, and the Holy Spirit. In love and joy, God creates and sustains the universe, including humanity, male and female, who are made in God’s image.God the FatherWe believe in God the Father Almighty, whose love is the foundation of salvation and righteous judgment, and who calls us into covenant relationship with God and with one another.God the SonWe believe in Jesus Christ, the Word, who is fully God and fully human. He came to show us God and perfect humanity, and, through his life, death, and resurrection, to reconcile us to God. He is now actively present with us as Savior, Teacher, Lord, and Friend.God the Holy SpiritWe believe in the Holy Spirit, who breathed God’s message into the prophets and apostles, opens our eyes to God’s Truth in Jesus Christ, empowers us for holy living, and carries on in us the work of salvation.SalvationWe believe that salvation comes through Jesus Christ alone, to whom we must respond with repentance, faith, and obedience. Through Christ we come into a right relationship with God, our sins are forgiven, and we receive eternal life.The BibleWe believe that God inspired the Bible and has given it to us as the uniquely authoritative, written guide for Christian living and thinking. The Scriptures are true and reliable. They point us to God, guide our lives, and nurture us toward spiritual maturity.The Christian LifeWe believe that God has called us to be and to make disciples of Jesus Christ and to be God’s agents of love and reconciliation in the world.The ChurchWe believe in the church as the people of God, composed of all who believe in Jesus Christ, who support and equip each other through worship, teaching, and accountability, who model God’s loving community, and who proclaim the gospel to the world.The FutureWe believe in the personal return of Jesus Christ, in the resurrection of the dead, in God’s judgment of all persons with perfect justice and mercy, and in eternal reward and punishment. Ultimately, Christ’s kingdom will be victorious over all evil, and the faithful will reign with him in eternal life.
column14: Morning Star Church exists to honor God by:Making disciples of JesusTraining disciples in the WordEmpowering disciples for ministry
column15: What should I expect in church?At Morning Star Church you can expect an exciting and energetic worship gathering with friendly people, good coffee, upbeat songs, and a casual atmosphere. You should feel right at home from the moment you step into the building.What should I wear?We’re more concerned with meeting your real life needs than with what you wear. Most people will dress in casual weekend attire, so dress how you feel comfortable and you’ll fit right in.What’s available for my kids?We have an excellent kid’s experience at Morning Star Church. Our trained volunteers will make sure the kids have an exciting and fun experience, learning about God and Biblical values. We believe your kids will look forward to being a part of this each time you come. Click here to see more details on our children’s programs.DiversityMorning Star Church is a community open to all people, regardless of where they are in their spiritual journey. This is a great place to meet a very diverse group of people and become a part of a supportive community that reaches out to those who are hurting, in need, or who just want to belong to something bigger than themselves.Practical TeachingCreative and relevant teaching is a priority at Morning Star Church. Pastor Josh loves to present the practical and timeless truths from the Bible with humor and sincerity. We hope you find the teaching inspiring and applicable to your everyday life.ConnectingOne of our main goals for every Sunday service is for people to be able to connect with God and with each other. We invite you to fill out the Communication Card, which is our way of knowing who you are, what kind of needs you might have, and how we can serve you better. Please stop by our guest services table to find out more ways to connect with others.

column13: The whole Bible is our sufficient rule for faith and practice. This Statement of Faith is intended as a basis of fellowship among us (i.e. that we all speak the same things, I Corinthians 1 - 10; Acts 2:42). 1. The Scriptures Inspired - We believe that the Bible is the inspired Word of God, a revelation from God to man, the infallible rule of faith and con duct, and is superior to conscience but not contrary to reason (II Timothy 3:15, 16; I Peter 2:2).2. The One True God - We believe that the One True God has revealed Himself in three persons, as Father, Son, and Holy Ghost. He is the eternally self-existing, self-revealed "I AM;" and has further revealed Himself as embodying the principles of Mark 12:29; Isaiah 43:10, 11; Matthew 28:19 and Luke 3:22.3. Man, His Fall & Redemption - We believe man was created good and upright; for God said, “Let us make man in our image, after our likeness.” But, man, by voluntary transgression, fell and his only hope of redemption is in Jesus Christ, the Son of God by the virtue of his shed blood on the cross. (Genesis 1:26 - 31; 3:1 - 7; Romans 5:12-21).4. The Salvation of Man - We believe that salvation comes through the Lord Jesus Christ, who was born of a virgin, willingly gave His life for us and rose again on the third day. Man is saved by the washing and the renewing of the Holy Ghost, and being justified by grace through faith, he becomes an heir of God according to the hope of eternal life (Titus 2:11; Romans 10:12 - 15; Luke 23:47; Titus 3:5 - 7).5. Baptism In Water - Water Baptism is an immersion in water representing an identification with the death, burial and resurrec­tion of Christ, having so done they have taken on the family name and hereby declare to the world that they have died with Jesus and that they have also been raise with Him to walk in newness of life (Matthew 28:19; Acts 10:47, 48; Romans 6:4; Acts 20:21; Hebrews 10:2 2). Infants and small children may be dedicated to the Lord whenever requested (Mark 10:16; Luke 18:15 -16).6. The Lord's Supper - The sacrament of the Lord's Supper is observed by partaking of bread and the fruit of the vine to represent, by faith, the virtue that was in the body and blood of the Lord. This is an act of sharing, one member with another, which brings a cleansing and unifying of the Body of Christ (I Corinthians 11:26).7. Promise of the Father - All believers are entitled to and should ardently expect and earnestly ask the promise of the Father - the Baptism in the Holy Spirit and the Fire, according to the command of our Lord Jesus Christ. This was the normal experience of all in the early Christian Church. With it comes Power for life and service, the bestowal of the gifts and their use in the work of the ministry (Luke 24:49; Acts 1:4, 8; I Corinthians 12:1 - 21). This wonderful experience is distinct from and subsequent to the experience of the new birth (Acts 10:44-46, 11:14-16, 15:7-9). The Baptism of believers in the Holy Ghost is evidenced by the initial physical sign of speaking with other tongues as the Spirit of God gives them utterance (Acts 2:4).8. Entire Sanctification - The Scriptures teach a life of holiness without which no man shall see the Lord. By the power of the Holy Ghost we are able to obey the command, “Be ye holy, for I am holy.” Entire sanctification is the will of God for all Believers (I Peter 1:15, 16; I Thessalonians 5:23; I John 2:6).9. The Church - The Church is the Body of Christ, the habitation of God through the Spirit, with divine appoint ments for the fulfillment of her great commission. Each believer, born of the Spirit, is an integral part of the Church of the Firstborn, which are written in Heaven (Ephesians 1:22, 23; Hebrews 12:23). Jesus is held in the heavens until the full restoration of a glorious church.10. The Ministry & Evangelism - A divinely called and Scripturally-ordained ministry has been provided by our Lord for a two-fold pur pose: The evangelization of the world and the edifying of the Body of Christ (Mark 16:15-20; Ephesians 4:13).11. Divine Healing - Deliverance from sickness is provided for in the atonement, and is the privilege of all Believers (Isaiah 54:4, 5; Matthew 8:16, 17).12. Laying On of Hands - God is ever unfolding truth such as the Laying On of Hands for gifts and ministries (I Timothy 4:14; Ephesians 4:11; I Corinthians 12).13. The Blessed Hope - The resurrection of those who have fallen asleep in Christ and their translation together with those who are alive and remain unto the coming of the Lord is the imminent and blessed hope of the Church (I Thessalonians 4:16, 17; Romans 8:23; Titus 2:13; I Corinthians 15:51, 52). 14. The Lake of Fire - The Devil and his angels, the Beast and the False Prophet, and whosoever is not found written in the Book of Life shall be consigned to everlasting punish ment in the lake which burneth with fire and brimsto ne, which is the second death (Revelation 19:20; 20:10-15).15. The New Heavens & The New Earth - We “according to His promise look for the new heaven and new earth wherein dwells righteousness.” (II Peter 3:13; Revelation 21:25).16. The God ordained sacrament of marriage in the Bible is defined as a legal union between one man and one woman for a lifetime, (Genesis 2:22-25 NKJV).

column12: We began this new church/mission as Bible study at Java Shop in San Francisco, Ca. The owners were professional Latin Jazz Artists and asked if I would bring a few guys from our Church to have a little coffee, some live music and a Bible Study.  People liked it so much, hearing the Jazz, Gospel and Blues they thought it was a night club. It became a church after one year. I had been in the ministry in San Jose, Ca. for over 20 years at the same church.  We knew right away God was taking us to a new place with a new approach that was outside of the box. We changed our dress code to everyday clothes; Jeans, Levi's and comfortable clothes, so that the people in the City would not feel they had to wear a suit, which in the Mission District most people did not have.  The Java Shop was located in the Mission District on 24th. and Potrero Ave. We named it 'THE MISSION 24' and our focus turned to people from the streets, those that were on drugs and homeless.  Our motto is 'Come to Jesus not Religion' Come as you are! Matthew 11:28.  I have four children ages from 11, 12, 14 and 25 been married for 26 years to my wife Rebecca. Since the beginning our Gospel Blues Band has played through out California at Bike and Car shows, Rely for Life Cancer Walk and for 6 Time World Boxing Champion Robert the Ghost Guerrero home coming in Gilroy, Ca. We also are very connected to CROSS Ministries: a motorcycle club based in Gilroy, Ca. We ride to events and outreaches in several communities across the bay area.  We use the Motorcycles as a tool to meet people on the streets and bring Jesus to them.
column13: We believe that Jesus Christ is Lord. When you come to Him you cannot come by your own good deeds. You must come by faith and grace. You must come as you are problems and all, its okay.We believe we are saved by grace, not by works. Ephesians  2:8-9 We believe Jesus Christ was God in the flesh according to the Scriptures. John 1:1-2 & 14; 1 Timothy 3:16We believe Jesus Christ literally rose from the dead after three days of being in the grave. 1 Corinthians 15:3-5We believe in the reconciliation of Jesus Christ and mankind. Every knee shall bow and every tongue shall confess that Jesus is Lord. Philippians 2:10-11We believe according to Acts 2:38 that you must be baptized in the name of Jesus Christ to enter into Heaven. We believe Jesus has created a perfect salvation. When you believe, you are justified unto salvation. Romans 10:10
column14: Our Mission StatementOur mission statement is based on Matthew 11:28 (King James Version): "Come unto Me, all you who labor and are heavy laden, and I will give you rest."The Message (New Bible Version) states: "Are you tired? Worn out? Burned out on religion? Come to Me. Get away ad you will recover your life. I will show you how to take a real rest."Our number one mission is to educate you about Jesus Christ freely. Come to Jesus, not to church. Come to Jesus, not to religion. Come meet your Father, your true friend and your guide for life and family.We accept all people regardless of background, social, economic and political affiliations.We help you break down barriers for those who are distressed, depressed, discontent, struggling financially or simply needing spiritual reinforcement.We teach the principles that are revealed in the Holy Scriptures pertaining to mankind's responsibilities dictated toward God and what is God's promise and faithfulness to mankind.We plan with God to restore as many lives as possible that have been destroyed by sin.
column15: When you come worship with us, you’ll first notice the warmth and genuineness of our members.  You can grab a cup of coffee before taking your seat. column12: Pastor Manuel Pereira has a zealous love for the Lord, a love for people, and a heart that desires to serve. Pastor Pereira is committed to accurate, clear, and passionate expositional preaching. He strives to prayerfully apply sound biblical exegesis as the basis for truthful and reliable teaching.Pastor Pereira is joyously married to his bride of over 15 years, Athena Pereira. They both enjoy a lovingly close relationship with their five children: Ashley, Junior, Joshua, Grace and Faith (twins). The Pereira family has lived in the general vicinity for approximately 12 years.As a former science and technology professional (see article), Pastor Pereira has gracefully departed from his career in research and has devoted himself to serving the Lord in full-time pastoral ministry, "for the equipping of the saints for the work of service, to the building up of the body of Christ." (Eph. 4:11)Pastor Pereira has started and seeks to maintain a biblical creation ministry, entitled Evolution-Exposed, from which he has presented several creation seminars. This ministry seeks to proclaim the word of God as authoritative in all matters of truth, and to demonstrate that wherever genuine empirical science is employed the Scripture stands thoroughly trustworthy.Pastor Pereira holds a Master of Divinity degree from The Master’s Seminary (listed in the TMS Alumni Directory).
column13: Section 1: The Word of GodWe believe that the Bible is the fully inspired Word of God, both the Old and New Testaments, and without error in the original manuscripts, written under the inspiration of the Holy Spirit, and that it has supreme authority in all matters of faith and conduct (John 17:17; Romans 15:4; II Timothy 3:16-17; II Peter 1:19-21).Section 2: The TrinityWe believe there is one living and true God, eternally existing in three persons – God the Father, God the Son, and God the Holy Spirit; that they are equal in every divine perfection; and that they execute distinct, but harmonious offices in the work of creation, providence, and redemption (Matthew 28:19; John 1:1-4; II Corinthians 13:14; Hebrews 9:14; Genesis 1:26).Section 3: God the FatherWe believe in God, the Father, an infinite personal spirit, perfect in holiness, wisdom, power and love. We believe that He concerns Himself mercifully in the affairs of men, that He hears and answers prayer, that He saves from sin and spiritual death all who come to Him through Jesus Christ (John 3:16-17; John 4:24; John 17:5).Section 4: Jesus ChristWe believe in Jesus Christ, God’s only begotten Son, who was conceived by the Holy Spirit. We believe in His virgin birth, sinless life, miracles and teachings. We believe in His substitutionary atoning death, bodily resurrection, ascension into heaven, perpetual intercession for His people, future return for His Church, and personal visible return to earth as King of Kings and Lord of Lords (Isaiah 7:14; John 1:14; Philippians 2:5-11; Hebrews 1:2-3; I John 1:7; I Thessalonians 4:16-17; Revelation 19:11-16).Section 5: The Holy SpiritWe believe in the Holy Spirit who came forth from the Father and Son to convict the world of sin, righteousness, and judgment; and to regenerate, sanctify, and empower all who believe in Jesus Christ. We believe that the Holy Spirit indwells every believer in Christ, and that He is an abiding helper, teacher, and guide (John 14:26; 16:7-15; Romans 8:14-17; Ephesians 1:13-14).Section 6: SalvationWe believe that all men are sinners by nature and by choice and are, therefore, under condemnation. We believe that those who repent of their sins and trust in Jesus Christ as Savior and Lord are saved from the penalty of sin, born again unto eternal life by the regenerating work of the Holy Spirit, and brought into personal fellowship with God. We believe that this salvation is a free gift from God, effected upon the ground of the shed blood of Jesus Christ alone, that it is given by grace and received by faith, and that apart from Jesus Christ salvation is impossible (John 1:12-13; 3:3, 16-17; Acts 4:12; 20:21; Ephesians 2:1-9; Titus 3:5).Section 7: The ChurchWe believe in the universal church, a living spiritual body of which Christ is the Head and all regenerated persons are members. We believe in the local church, consisting of a company of believers in Jesus Christ, who have been baptized by immersion subsequent to profession of their faith in Christ, and who are associated for worship, work, and fellowship. We believe that God has laid upon the members of the local church the primary task of giving the gospel of Jesus Christ to a lost world (Matthew 16:16-18; Acts 2:38-41; Ephesians 2:19-22; 5:25-27; Matthew 28:18-20).Section 8: Christian ConductWe believe that a Christian should live for the glory of God and the well-being of his fellow men, that his conduct should be blameless before the world, that he should be a faithful steward of his possessions, and that he should seek to realize for himself and others the full stature of maturity in Christ (Matthew 5:16; II Corinthians 9:6-8; Ephesians 4:11-16; Philippians 2:14-16; Colossians 3:17-23;I Thessalonians 5:17-18).Section 9: The OrdinancesWe believe that the Lord Jesus Christ has committed two ordinances to the local church, baptism and the Lord’s Supper. We believe that Christian baptism is the immersion of a believer in water into the Name of the triune God. We believe that the Lord’s Supper was instituted by Christ for commemoration of His death. We believe that the two ordinances should be observed and administered until the return of the Lord Jesus Christ (Matthew 28:18-20; Acts 2:41; 8:38-39; I Corinthians 11:23-32).Section 10: Religious LibertyWe believe that every human being has direct relations with God, and is responsible to God alone in all matters of faith; that each church is independent and must be free from interference by an ecclesiastical or political authority; that, therefore, Church and State must be kept separate as having different functions, each fulfilling its duties free from dictation or patronage of the other (Matthew 22:21; Acts 4:18-19, 29; Romans 13:7; I Peter 2:9).Section 11: The Last ThingsWe believe in the personal and visible return of the Lord Jesus Christ to earth and the establishment of His kingdom. We believe in the resurrection of the body, the final judgment, the eternal blessedness of the saved, and the endless suffering of the lost (Matthew 25:31-46; John 5:28-29;II Corinthians 5:10; Revelation 20:1-15).Section 12: Theological PerspectiveThe teaching and practice of Trinity Bible Church shall be that which is consistent with our belief in 1) the premillennial return of Christ, 2) the pretribulational rapture of the church, and 3) the “non-charismatic” understanding of the existence and practice of spiritual gifts, (Zechariah 14; Revelation 20:1-6; I Thessalonians 4:16-18; Revelation 3:10; I Corinthians 13:8-12; I Peter 4:10,11).

column12: Raised in the Bay Area, I describe my religious background "CathoBaptist." I went to catholic schools grades 1-12, while actively attending a Baptist church. I developed an awe and respect for clergy and anything religious in early elementary school. When I became an altarboy, and a parishioner discover I'd no confirmation, I was "dismissed" from my duties ... a sixth grader and a altarboy has-been. I volunteered when they asked for volunteers because of the draw to serve in that role. Ironically, the confirmed Catholics refused to serve, so I volunteered, ignorant of the prerequisite of confirmation. The draw to serve in sacred spaces threads through my high school years as a junior deacon in my baptist church home, 4 years at Morehouse College where I served as a chapel assistant treasurer. More formally, completed an M.Div. degree at ITC and Ph.D. coursework at Emory University. I'm a gadget-man, a married parent of 3 children, and I love music and hifi stereo equipment, working with males in the area of spiritual identity formation-- the most exciting and challenging work I do.Additionally, I serve as the dean of counseling and student support at Los Medanos College.
column13: We believe in the INCARNATION of Christ and express this organizationally through CONGREGATIONAL POLITY, everyone is informed about and votes on major church initiatives. We also believe in the practice of WATER IMMERSION as a sign that people have chosen to become a follower of Christ, and live so that others will more clearly see Him.MINISTRY-- We believe that God endows every believer with special gifts that are to be employed for the health and progress of the church and community.MAGNIFICATION-- We believe that worship is vital to clarify the direction of our lives and fuel them with utimacy and joy. Worship should fuel you to want to face the next day. MEMBERSHIP-- We believe that we are made, not for life-in-isolation but life-in- intentional-fellowship, where personal joys and sorrows are shared. The saying,"Laugh, the world laughs with you; cry, cry alone," is a very often true but bogus saying that we refuse to live out. You can only experience God in community.MULTIPLICATION-- We believe that who we are evolves and deepens only as we learn more about the Christ who calls us into relationship. You can't wipe someone's tears while Skyping.MULTIPLYING-- We believe that, by sharing the personal story of our faith journey with Christ, we carry out the primary intention of the Church, which is to give people the hope of transformation from wondedness to health, from self-centeredness to other-centeredness, fromChrist as a crisis- response to Christ as the power alive within, from secrecy about the experience of Christ alive within to shsring of option to experience Christ as the one who offers restoration for the wounded, violated and breached of us parts-- all if us!
column14: We are an intentionally multi-generational and multicultural congregation that thrives by offering life-transforming experiences to people in the San Mateo Peninsula who seek to explore and discover meaningful ways to respond to Christ's call to relationship with more and more of their lives.
column15: You'll experience authentic warmth, that people here are real. You'll see people who will call or visit you while you're in the hospital.
