column12: The Reverend Doctor W. James Favorite was born in Vacherie, Louisiana, the third son of a family of five boys and one girl.  He is a graduate of Southern University in Baton Rough, Louisiana where he earned both a Bachelor's and Master's of Science Degree in Health, Physical Education and Social Studies.  He attended the Virginia Seminary and College of Lynchburg, Virginia, where he earned both a Bachelor of Arts in Religion in  1995 and a Masters of Divinity in Theology in 1997.  IN December of 1990, Rev. Favorite received an Honorary Doctor of Divinity Degree from the Maryland Theological Seminary and College for his outstanding work in the ministry.  He continued his studies at this institution and in June 1995 he earned the Doctor of Ministry Degree.Rev. Favorite was licensed to preach the Gospel in July 1984.  He was ordained on September 13, 1985 by Morning Star Baptist Church in Catonsville, Maryland, where he served as Pastor from April 1987 until he was called to Beulah Baptist Institutional Church, Tampa, Florida in August 1995.He has been called a friend, a wise counselor, a biblical preacher, and an obedient, caring servant of God.  His primary agenda is Kingdom Building and his high energy has taken him from the walls of Beulah Baptist Institutional Church out into the communities of Tampa, to the local politicians, to the State Representatives in Tallahassee, to the Congressional and Senatorial Representatives in our Nations Capital.  He believes in education and believes that every man, woman and child deserves a fair chance.  He believes in that the community can be a better place for everyone if every person would give just a tenth of their time or talent.Pastor Favorite has been active in many community organizations and has served on many committees since moving to Tampa.  Included are Pastors on Patrol, the African American Family Support Initiative, Childcare Facilities Advisory Board, Urban League Board, and the list goes on.  He recently completed four years of service as President of the Congress in the Progressive National Baptist Convention, Southern Region.Beulah Baptist has experienced much growth in membership, faithful giving and Christian Education since Rev. Favorite accepted the call as Pastor.  He came with a Vision to lead Beulah into the 21st Century and he has shared this Vision with many in the Tampa Pastoral Community.   HE is committed to teaching other ministers to preach and has demonstrated this initiative by sponsoring a biweeklyEffective Preaching class that is free to all that would come.Dr. Favorite is married to Dr. Ann Fuller Favorite.  They have two adult children, Rodney of Baltimore, Maryland and Andrea of Los Angeles, California and one grandchild, Master Hashim Favorite of Baltimore.
column13: How to be saved is the most important quest of any human life. This quest begins when a man or woman first realizes their true state before a holy God. The intimate and sweet fellowship that the Father longed for with man, the crown of His creation, was lost when Adam and Eve disobeyed God's commandment in the Garden of Eden. When Adam and Eve sinned they lost their right to eat of the tree of life which would have enabled them to live forever. They were expelled from the garden and as such denied the loving relationship that God desired to have with them. Their sinful state made them unfit to linger in the presence of God. Far from being a minor event, this Fall and expulsion of man was the cataclysmic turning point of history and set humanity on a descent which continues to this day. Man without God makes his own plans, follows his own counsels and lives by his own rules. Nevertheless, because man was created for fellowship with God, there remains a dissatisfaction and longing within man that can only be fulfilled by God Himself. As man is now hopelessly decadent and God is perfectly holy, there exists the need for God and man to be reconciled so that the fellowship may be restored. How to be saved -- What has God provided for man's salvation?How to be saved has been outlined for every man in the preaching of the Gospel. The Gospel is the good news about Jesus Christ. For God was in Christ, reconciling the world to himself, no longer counting people's sins against them. . . (2 Corinthians 5:19). God, fully knowing that man would fall, provided a means of reconciliation for man; He knew that there was nothing that a man could do to make mankind acceptable to God. God sent Jesus Christ, who provided restoration for man with God by giving His own life, shedding His own blood. There was no other way to eradicate the effect of sin except by blood ... without the shedding of blood, there is no forgiveness of sins (Hebrews 9:22). This shedding of blood indicated that the penalty for sin had been paid; a life had been sacrificed for the lives of all who have sinned. Jesus Christ's willing submission to the massacre on the cross paid the price for our sins and affected the means of reconciliation. Because one person disobeyed God, many people became sinners. But because one other person obeyed God, many people will be made right in God's sight (Romans 5:19). How to be saved -- What must a man do to be saved?How to be saved is within the reach of every human being on the face of the earth. When Jesus Christ died on the cross, He provided salvation for all. "And when I am lifted up on the cross, I will draw everyone to myself." He said this to indicate how he was going to die (John 12:32-33). Salvation has been provided; it now must be accepted. Once a man or woman recognizes the need for salvation and realizes that God has provided for their salvation through Jesus Christ, he or she must go on to embrace it. Salvation is simply a process of confessing and believing. A man must confess that Jesus is Lord, which signifies his realization that Christ must have full rule over his life with all of His righteous requirements. This confession of Christ as Lord also assumes that it is Christ who will work and fulfill His own righteousness within man. Next, he must believe that God has raised Jesus Christ from the dead. This belief in the death and resurrection of Jesus carries with it the realization that the penalty has been paid for sin and power is provided for man to live a life free from sin. Thus man's relationship to God is restored. For if you confess with your mouth that Jesus is Lord and believe in your heart that God raised him from the dead, you will be saved. For it is by believing in your heart that you are made right with God, and it is by confessing with your mouth that you are saved. As the Bible tells us, For if you confess with your mouth that Jesus is Lord and believe in your heart that God raised him from the dead, you will be saved. For it is by believing in your heart that you are made right with God, and it is by confessing with your mouth that you are saved (Romans 10:9-11). Do you feel unworthy to go to heaven? Peace with God is within your reach.Do you understand that you are a sinner, and you believe that Jesus Christ came as the one and only Redeemer of sin? Are you ready to receive God's gift of His Son, Jesus Christ? If so, believe in Christ, repent of your sins, and commit the rest of your life to Him as Lord: Father, I know that I have broken your laws and my sins have separated me from you. I am truly sorry, and now I want to turn away from my past sinful life toward you. Please forgive me, and help me avoid sinning again. I believe that your son, Jesus Christ died for my sins, was resurrected from the dead, is alive, and hears my prayer. I invite Jesus to become the Lord of my life, to rule and reign in my heart from this day forward. Please send your Holy Spirit to help me obey You, and to do Your will for the rest of my life. In Jesus' name I pray, Amen."Repent, and let every one of you be baptized in the name of Jesus Christ for the remission of sins; and you shall receive the gift of the Holy Spirit." (Acts 2:38)If you decided receive Jesus today, welcome to God's family. Now, as a way to grow closer to Him, the Bible tells us to follow up on our commitment.Get baptized as commanded by Christ.Tell someone else about your new faith in Christ.Spend time with God each day. It does not have to be a long period of time. Just develop the daily habit of praying to Him and reading His Word. Ask God to increase your faith and your understanding of the Bible.Seek fellowship with other followers of Jesus. Develop a group of believing friends to answer your questions and support you.Find a local church where you can worship God.

column12: Hi, this is Tony Byrd, and I've served as Lead Pastor here at MorningStar since our launch back in 2000.  Ours is a church that is very serious about our commitment to Christ, and also our subsequent mission in this world, which is, as we say, to connect and effect.  However, we don't take ourselves too seriously in the process.  We're a pretty laid back crew in that regard, with some of the more genuine, compassionate, family-oriented people you'll find anywhere.  If you can't tell, I'm pretty fond of them!About the only things more important to me in life, in fact, are my relationship with Jesus and my family ¦ principally my wonderful wife, Heather, and my four crazy kids.  I also have a great love for sports, music, reading, travel, and all things Florida Gator, but don't hold that against me (ha!).  Come see us sometime!
column13: What We BelieveAbout the BibleWe believe that the Bible is the inspired, infallible and authoritative written Word of God, and that it is the all-sufficient guide for believers.About GodWe believe that there is only one living and true God, and that He is an infinitely holy, powerful, intelligent, present, merciful, loving and personal Being. Further, He eternally exists in three persons: God the Father, God the Son, and God the Holy Spirit.About JesusWe believe that Jesus Christ is the eternal, divine Son of God who came to this earth in human flesh, conceived of the Holy Spirit and born of the Virgin Mary, to become the Savior of the world. Fully God and fully man, He lived a sinless life, was crucified and buried, rose from the dead, ascended to Heaven, and today sits at the right hand of God the Father as our intercessor.About Sin and SalvationWe believe that all have sinned and come short of the glory of God, and as such all are eternally separated from Him. Forgiveness, grace, and salvation (new life), however, are freely offered to all who believe in and accept Jesus Christ as Lord and Savior. No one can earn it, but anyone can receive it.About the Holy SpiritWe believe that the Holy Spirit is the Spirit of God Himself who works to exalt Jesus Christ, convict and regenerate sinful humanity, and sanctify, encourage, teach and strengthen believers. We believe that a person is filled with the in-dwelling of the Holy Spirit at the moment he or she accepts Jesus Christ as Savior. We also believe in the subsequent baptism of the Holy Spirit as a special enduement of power for all believers who ask, enabling them to become supernaturally-empowered witnesses of the love of Jesus Christ. Further, we believe in the present-day operation of all the gifts of the Spirit listed in the Word of God.About Baptism and Holy CommunionWe believe each believer, following the example and commandment of Christ, should experience water baptism (by immersion) in the name of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit. For the believer this is an outward testimony of an inner change.We believe in Holy Communion, or the Lord's Supper, as a symbolic act of obedience in which believers receive bread and juice to memorialize the sacrificial, redemptive death of Jesus and anticipate His second coming.About the ChurchWe believe that the Church is of divine origin, a living organism with Christ as the Head. It is a people, not a place but a spiritual body of born again believers manifesting the gifts and fruit of the Holy Spirit. Its purposes are to worship God through exalting His Son, Jesus Christ; to build edifying relationships with others; to declare the good news of Jesus Christ to a lost and dying world; to disciple all believers in growing relationships with Jesus Christ; and to minister love and care to all who are in need.About StewardshipRecognizing that God is the Source of all temporal and spiritual blessings, we believe that all believers are obligated to sacrificially serve Him with their time, talents and material possessions.About ServingWe believe that service within the Body of Christ is mandated in God's Word. God has equipped each of us with natural abilities and spiritual gifts that are designed to be used to build up the entire Body and to reach those who do not have a relationship with God. We believe it is the responsibility of each believer to use his or her unique gifts in an area of ongoing service.About Last ThingsWe believe God, in His own time and in His own way, will bring the world to its appropriate end. According to His promise, Jesus Christ will return personally and visibly in glory to the earth; the dead will be raised; and all living believers will be raptured away. Christ will then judge all humanity in righteousness. The unrighteous will be consigned to eternal punishment, but the righteous in their resurrected and glorified bodies will be rewarded and will forever live in Heaven with the Lord.
column14: Our PurposeFollowing the pattern of the New Testament church, we're here to CONNECT and EFFECT in the following five ways:Worship: We exist to connect with God in worship by exalting His Son, Jesus Christ, and effect lifestyles of worship in those to whom we minister.Relationships: We desire to connect people in meaningful, life-giving relationships. Our goal is to effect unity in the Body of Christ and demonstrate the love of Jesus to all.Evangelism: We exist to connect those who do not yet know Jesus Christ with His love and life-changing power, and help effect meaningful transformation in the hearts and lives of thousands.Discipleship: We exist to connect new and current believers with a continuing and growing relationship with Jesus Christ, and effect spiritual maturity and formation in the lives of every believer.Servant Ministry: We exist to connect with believers and non-believers in relevant, servant-oriented ministry and care. Our goal is to effect an attitude of caregiving within the body of Christ and a change in the spiritual climate of our city and our world.Our Shaping ValuesWe believe that:1. People matter most to God, and as a result our mission to "connect and effect" is the most important mission on the planet. 2. God requires us to both love AND live like Christ -- modeling grace, pursuing holiness. 3. 	A quest for excellence in all things is non-negotiable. 4. 	High-capacity leadership and humble-hearted servanthood are equally critical to the success of the mission. 5. The day we cease to be culturally-relevant and/or doctrinally pure is the day we should voluntarily shut our doors. 6. We can't put a price tag on our character and integrity. 7. No amount of talent, creativity or hard work will ever replace the guidance and strength of the Holy Spirit.

column12: I've been with Valley Baptist Church in Castro Valley for 21 years. We are a small friendly church where the Bible is central. We study it on Saturdays and Sundays and we have 2-3 good teachers who teach. We have SUNDAY_SCHOOL, at 9:30 and worship at 11:00 am. Join us if you are seeking to know God and want to start out small. You will find us a friendly loving group. Your questions are always welcome.
column13: We follow the Baptist Faith and Message statement of the So. Baptist Convention of California. Look at their website for more info.
column14: Our vision and purpose is to help people fulfill the purposes of God: salvation through Jesus Christ and church membership, to grow in maturity through Bible Study, ministry and fellowship, witness of one's faith to others and glorify God through worship.
column15: Coming to visit Valley is like a breath of fresh air. YOU will be loved, greeted and welcomed. In our worship service you will experience joy, friendship and the presence of God. The message is Christ centered and Bible oriented;  designed to meet needs encourage and motivate one to serve God out of faith and through His grace. The music if contemporary and uplifting. Join us we are not stuffy or boring.
column18: We cooperate with the So. Baptist Convention and are a mission supporting internationally minded fellowship.

column12: My name is Kevin Waldrop, and I have been the senior pastor at Village Baptist Church for almost seven years. My wife's name is Janet, and we have five beautiful daughters. Our oldest daughter is almost 11 and the youngest almost 1. My wife and I are originally from northeast Mississippi and moved to the Bay Area in order to answer the call to pastor Village Baptist Church. We enjoy the outdoors and hiking with our children. I have a Master's of Divinity from Golden Gate Baptist Theological Seminary and am currently enrolled in their Ph.D. program. I believe the Bible to be the infallible and inerrant word of God, and I seek to keep the preaching and teaching of the word at the center of my ministry.
column13: We are a Southern Baptist Congregation and therefore affirm the beliefs set forth in the Baptist Faith and Message (http://www.sbc.net/bfm/bfm2000.asp). A few specific things:1. We believe the Bible to be the authoritative word of God, applicable to every life situation in directing believers in word and practice.2. We believe that salvation is found in Jesus Christ alone. We hold to the five solas: Salvation is by grace alone, through faith alone, in Christ alone, according to the Scriptures alone, for the glory of God alone.3. We believe that all who have trusted Jesus as Lord and Savior should formally associate with a local body of believers for the purpose of growing in the faith and carrying out the work of the kingdom on earth.
column14: Our mission involves the equipping of all the saints for the work of the ministry (Eph. 4:12). Our vision involves the ongoing maturity of every believer so that we all as one are united in our mission to glorify God by obeying Him and walking in His ways. Specifically this obedience is manifest in our proclamation of the gospel of Jesus Christ to the world. This proclamation involves both our intentional speaking the truth in love and our loving obedience to God's word.
column15: To all who desire to know what the Bible says, and to anyone looking to serve God obediently through the local church, I invite you to come and worship with us at Village Baptist Church. I am not perfect, and our church is not perfect, but we are committed to the word of God, and we desire to grow in our love for one another and our commitment to Jesus Christ our Savior. Through the power and direction of the Holy Spirit, we can be all that God would have us be. To God be the glory!                                                                        -Pastor Kevin Waldrop
column18: Village Baptist Church is a part of East Bay Baptist Association, California Southern Baptist Convention, and the Southern Baptist Convention.

column12: Pastor Chuck was raised in Baltimore MD, served in Vietnam with the US Navy including two years in the Race Relations Department (1970-74), graduated from California Baptist University 1978, served churches in Menifee Valley CA, Fort Worth TX, Lomita CA, Dixon CA before coming to Calvary in October of 1990. Since then, we have launched three congregations in Korean, Spanish and Tagalog. We are nurturing new ministries on site in Spanish and Vietnamese. We also host a non-denominational Chinese church and a Pentecostal church.Networkers seek mutually beneficial relationships. Our pastor is a Net-Weaver, connecting others to serve together for the benefit of our community, including Evangelical Churches of the Hayward Area, HayWallKru, Hayward Alliance for Arts Education, Hayward Chamber Of Commerce Ambassador, Hayward Coalition for Healthy Youth, Hayward Education Foundation, Hayward Neighborhood Alert, Hayward Rotary, Keep Hayward Clean & Green Task Force, Latino Business Roundtable, Partners In Education, PC Community President, Court Appointed Special Advocate for foster children.In the past he has served Be A Mentor, Hayward Adult School/Technology Volunteer, Hayward Area Historical Society/Community Advisory Committee, Hayward-Ghazni Afghanistan Sister City Committee, Hayward JayceesHis wife, Linda, is a bookkeeper, leads Bible study on Sunday mornings and Thursday evenings, and leads in area women’s ministries. Their grown children serve the Lord and raise their children to also love Jesus. Christal and Thomas are in Long Beach CA with their boys Keagan and Bayden. Aaron and Cathy have Maelani, Arianna and Elijah in San Ramon. Aaron is a founder of the Soulciety.org ministry.
